# Checkpoint Persistence

After substantial work, update the project memory when any of these occur:

- A bug root cause is confirmed
- A migration is added
- A PR is merged
- Runtime behavior changes
- A major UI or status semantic changes
- A new architectural rule is established
- A meaningful next step is identified

Update (vault root first, else seed path):

`02 - Projects/GithubArchiver/Current Status.md`

Also sync the same durable facts into `docs/ai-memory/seed/02 - Projects/GithubArchiver/Current Status.md` when the vault is unavailable so the next session still has continuity.

Include:

- Date
- What changed
- Why it changed
- Tests added
- Deployment state
- Remaining verification steps

Do not write speculative conclusions as facts.
Do not dump full chat transcripts into the vault.
